  "notes": [
    "This is a non-inverting Schmitt trigger using one section of the LM393.",
    "R1 and R2 create a fixed reference: VREF = VDD × R2 / (R1 + R2). With R1 = R2 and VDD = 5.00 V, VREF = 2.50 V.",
    "VIN is applied through R4 to the non-inverting summing node IN1+ rather than directly to the comparator input.",
    "R5 feeds back the output voltage to IN1+ and creates hysteresis.",
    "The switching condition is VIN(th) = VREF × (1 + R4/R5) - VOUT × (R4/R5).",
    "With R4 = 10.0 kΩ and R5 = 49.9 kΩ, R4/R5 ≈ 0.2004.",
    "When VOUT is LOW, the rising threshold is approximately 3.001 V.",
    "When VOUT is HIGH, the falling threshold is approximately 1.999 V.",
    "These thresholds satisfy the 3.0 V rising and 2.0 V falling requirements within ±0.1 V.",
    "R3 provides the required pull-up for the LM393 open-collector output.",
    "U1 pin 7 (OUT2) is intentionally unconnected.",
    "U1 pins 5 and 6 are tied to GND so the unused comparator does not float.",
    "Use a regulated 5.00 V supply and precision resistors to preserve threshold accuracy."
  ]
